cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper discusses the use of universal sentence representations for evaluating machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves training sentence representations using large-scale data, which is a common technique in machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL), making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper uses experimental results and performance evaluation, which are common in computer vision (CV) and neural networks (NE), making cs.CV and cs.NE possible sub-categories.
